  "prompt": "Where can I get Marvel comics free?",
  "response": "You can find Marvel comics for free through several legitimate avenues:\n\n1. **Marvel\u2019s Official Website**: Marvel occasionally offers free comic issues on their website. Check their site for any promotional free comics.\n\n2. **ComiXology**: This digital comic platform sometimes has free comics available, including selections from Marvel. Look out for their free section or special promotions.\n\n3. **Library Services**: Many public libraries offer access to digital comic services like Hoopla or OverDrive. If you have a library card, you can borrow digital versions of Marvel comics for free.\n\n4. **Marvel Unlimited**: While it's a paid subscription service, Marvel Unlimited often offers free trial periods during which you can access a vast library of comics.\n\n5. **Free Comic Book Day**: Held annually, local comic book shops often participate by giving away free comic books, including special Marvel editions. Check for events in your area.\n\n6. **Special Promotions and Events**: Keep an eye out for special promotions on websites or in comic shops, especially around significant movie releases or anniversaries.\n\nRemember to always use legal and legitimate sources to access comics.",
